(300,	8,	'2017-11-24 12:03:12',	'2017-11-24 04:03:12',	'Hawker centers are a unique part of Singaporean culture. Serving as important community hubs, they’ve developed into popular areas for food and drink with adjoining markets and lively atmospheres. The selection is huge and typically served with rice, customers can select from many, many dishes. Awesome selection, atmosphere and food. They’ve come a long way since they were formed as an answer to rapid population growth in the 50s and 60s and now, they feature some highly-rated homemade and authentic cuisine that is perfect for return customers or curious investigators. Vegetarian food from hawker centers in Singapore is an easy, delicious and affordable choice for anyone. \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/11/Hawker-center-300x190.jpg\" alt=\"Hawker center\" width=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-303\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Delicious Vegetarian Food from Hawker Centers in Singapore</h2> \r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Redhill Market and Food Centre</h3>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/11/Red-Hill-Delicious-Vegetarian-Food-300x223.jpg\" alt=\"Red Hill - Delicious Vegetarian FoodRed Hill - Delicious Vegetarian Food\" width=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-306\" />\r\n\r\nRedhill Market and Food Centre attracts huge crowds for lunch and breakfast daily. Established since the 70s, it has so many delicious and authentic food outlets scattered throughout its large size and many high-rated vendors see queues out the door for breakfast meals! Vegetarian cuisine is this center’s main game and it’s especially popular. \r\n\r\nNotable stalls are numerous and include Ru Yi Yuan Vegetarian Food which serves great and inexpensive bee hoon amongst other varied dishes. \r\n\r\nHong Seung Curry Rice have been established for three generations and with tons of rice dishes on offer, they’re sure to satisfy any type of eater.\r\n\r\nThere are sweet dishes on offer too, like the stall named Delicious Fried Carrot Cake which sells fine quality carrot cake with some crunch. \r\n\r\nJi Xiang Ru Yi Vegetarian serves a vegetarian Bee Hoon with crisp high quality bean curd and plenty of other great ingredients.\r\n<strong>\r\nAddress</strong> :  85 Redhill Ln, Singapore 150085.\r\n\r\n<h3>Holland Drive Food Centre</h3>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/11/Holland-Drive-Food-Centre-Delicious-Vegetarian-FOod-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Holland Drive Food Centre Delicious Vegetarian FOod\" width=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-304\" />\r\n\r\nHolland Drive Food Centre features tons of excellent vendors who specialise in an assortment of dishes including many sought-after vegetarian dishes. Some stalls here look pretty swanky, clearly they’ve been successful in the game for years - often decades. One such acclaimed dish is Rojak, from the stall named Rojak Line. Their foodee-worthy Rojak offering is made with vegetarian shrimp-style paste. It comes with various veg, fruits, your tiao, tau pok and nuts. You reportedly can’t tell it apart from actual shrimp paste!\r\n\r\nMore veggie dishes come in the form of toasted you tiao popiah which uses the same special vegetarian shrimp paste with peanuts, wrapped in a popiah skin. \r\n\r\nHakka Noodles offers up awesome vegetarian bee hoon noodles at Holland Drive. There aren’t many stalls here but what this hawker lacks in quantity it makes up in quality. \r\n\r\n<strong>Address :</strong> 44 Holland Dr, Singapore 270044\r\n\r\n<h3>14 Haig Road Market - Wang Jiao Vegetarian Food</h3> \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/11/Wang-Jiao-Vegetarian-Food-Delicious-Vegetarian-Food-300x206.jpg\" alt=\"Wang Jiao Vegetarian Food Delicious Vegetarian Food\" width=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-308\" />\r\n\r\nThe 4 Haig Road hawker centre where you can find Wang Jiao Vegetarian Food houses some of the most reputable Malay stalls in Singapore. Amongst some top quality offerings, Wang Jiao Vegetarian nestles near to the top spot and serves up a huge menu of great dishes including their famous Fish Bean Soup, which features mock fish. This mock fish is boiled, not fried but still retains plenty of appealing texture and flavour. \r\n\r\nNext up, their dumplings contain tasty textured vegetable protein with seasoning and noodles. Boths dishes have a great modest simplicity which disguises tastiness at a real low price. \r\n\r\n<strong>Address : </strong>#01-35, 14, Haig Rd, Singapore 430014 Haig Rd, Singapore 430014 \r\n\r\n<h3>Taman Jurong Market and Food Centre - Poh Meng Vegetarian Food</h3>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/11/Poh-Meng-Delicious-Vegetarian-Food-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"Poh Meng Delicious Vegetarian Food\" width=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-305\" />\r\n\r\nPoh Meng Vegetarian food near Taman Jurong Food Centre usually sells out by 2pm with their tremendous selection of vegetarian food. It’s a well organised, clean and modern hawker and its market is often bustling, brimming with top-notch authentic offerings. Some top dishes including a bee hoon with great gravy, extensive veg and tons of juicy goodness. This stall really shows how hawker centres can offer top cuisine at low prices. It will definitely have you coming back for more. \r\n\r\nFo Shou Vegetarian Food is another acclaimed member of the Taman Jurong Market and Food Centre who are known for their remarkable vegetable prawn noodles which make a bold stab at recreating prawn texture and flavour in a healthy veg friendly dish. \r\n\r\n<strong>Address : </strong>Taman Jurong Food Market Centre\r\n#03-143 Yung Sheng Road Singapore 618499\r\n\r\n<h3>79A Circuit Rd - Victor’s Vegetarian Food</h3> \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/11/Victors-Vegetarian-Food-300x223.jpg\" alt=\"Victor&#039;s Vegetarian Food\" width=\"600\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-307\" />\r\n\r\nVegetarian food in block 79A down Circuit Road illustrates some of Singapore\'s awesome selection of vegetarian food. It’s 40% vegetarian food - you really are spoilt for choice. One vendor is Victor’s, who sells burgers alongside vegetarian Otah. This is a rare and tricky dish. With lemongrass flavours combined with fragrant pandan and chilli, this dish really packs some great flavours. A great find!\r\n\r\nAnother notable vegetarian stall named Choo Zai Zhai Vegetarian is renowned for its mock oyster dishes. Fried oyster omelette with hokkien mee is reportedly excellent, a real standout at a hawker that offers over 10 vegetarian stalls!\r\n<strong>\r\nAddress : </strong>Block 79A, Circuit Road Singapore\r\n',	'5 Delicious Vegetarian Food from Hawker Centers in Singapore',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'5-delicious-vegetarian-food-from-hawker-centers-in-singapore',	'',	'',	'2017-11-24 12:03:12',	'2017-11-24 04:03:12',	'',	0,	'https://waitrr.com/?p=300',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
