e right texture - neither dry nor moist and sticky. Lynn does full-blown large rainbow cakes to go too, so don’t settle at a single slice if you want more!\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/lynnscakes/\">https://www.facebook.com/lynnscakes/</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Lynda Ann</h3>\r\n<img class=\"img-responsive alignnone wp-image-349 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/12/Lynda-Ann-Waitrr.png\" alt=\"Lynda Ann Waitrr\" width=\"699\" height=\"463\" />\r\n\r\nLynda Ann’s selection of fine baked cakes and goodies is epic. She pursued a passion for baking since childhood and her creations have been perfected since then. One of her best sellers is the rainbow cake, which looks amazing. The 6 neat layers are perfectly balanced and they’re sandwiched traditionally between icing and cream. These amazingly well formed slices taste every bit as good as they look and they’re sure to satisfy any cake eater, from adults to children.\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/lynda.ann.cakes/\">https://www.facebook.com/lynda.ann.cakes/</a>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>The Coffee Daily</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_350\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"700\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-350 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/12/The-Coffee-Daily-Waitrr.png\" alt=\"The Coffee Daily Waitrr\" width=\"700\" height=\"464\" /> Photo source : https://sg.openrice.com/en/singapore/article/best-heartland-cafes-in-singapore-a1091[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe Coffee Daily’s laid back premises makes it perfect for breakfast, lunch or snacks. A lovely coffee shop known for its cooked and freshly prepared breakfasts, The Coffee Daily has refined its menu and added vibrant cakes and sweets to their repertoire. Among their wide array of brilliantly baked goods is their special rainbow cake. Encased in chocolate and lovingly adorned in sprinkles, this rainbow cake punches a sweetness that is up to the highest standard of the sweetest tooth around! This technicolour cake is succulent, indulgent and just so tasty that you’ll be counting your calories for second slice!\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/thecoffeedaily75/?fref=ts\">https://www.facebook.com/thecoffeedaily75/?fref=ts</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>I am… Cafe</h3>\r\n<img class=\"img-responsive alignnone wp-image-351 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/12/I-am-Cafe-Waitrr.png\" alt=\"I am Cafe Waitrr\" width=\"702\" height=\"391\" />\r\n\r\nI am... Cafe specialises in all manner of brunches and deserts has in their awesome menu their glorious rainbow cake with no less than 7 layers. Yep, that’s one more than the other cakes here and each layer is generous too! In fact, you can hardly call this a slice, it’s a slab! Moreover, the vibrant layers are composed of traditional sponge cake and the cream cheese filling and casing is tangy, sweet and well-textured. We can’t emphasize enough how massive this is so if you’re looking forward to trying it, don’t fill yourself up too much first! What\'s more, I am... Cafe is available on <a href=\"https://waitrr.com/\">Waitrr</a>. That means you\'ll be able to order your rainbow cakes before even getting to the cafe beating the wait.\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Iamathajilane/\">https://www.facebook.com/Iamathajilane/</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Dean and Deluca</h3>\r\n<img class=\"img-responsive alignnone wp-image-352 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/12/Dean-and-Deluca-Waitrr.png\" alt=\"Dean and Deluca Waitrr\" width=\"700\" height=\"462\" />\r\n\r\nDean and Deluca is a diverse shop serving gourmet offerings of varying kinds. With a wide array of pastries, all day breakfasts and many other delectable snacks for any time of day, Dean and Deluca’s rainbow cake is a real standout. Different from the rest listed here, it’s not just a pretty vanilla or otherwise traditional sponge, but a fruit cocktail of flavours. It has orange, lemon, blueberry, grapefruit and strawberry sections, all made with their own natural flavourings and extracts. If that isn\'t enough, the cream topping looks quite amazing. It’s a real best seller and it’s easy to see why - this slice of cake is perfect for the ‘gram or for eating at any time it takes your fancy (and that’s often!)\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/DeanDelucaSG/\">https://www.facebook.com/DeanDelucaSG/</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Know any delicious rainbow cakes in Singapore you think should be added to the list? Let us know in the comments below!</strong>',	'7 Rainbow Cakes in Singapore to Liven Up Any Party',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'344-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2017-12-19 14:40:43',	'2017-12-19 06:40:43',	'',	344,	'https://waitrr.com/344-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(358,	8,	'2017-12-27 09:00:07',	'2017-12-27 01:00:07',	'Remember the cute Disney Dim Sum characters from Hong Kong Disneyland flooding our social media accounts? Weren\'t they just so cute and tempting to bite into? While having our very own Disneyland with these cute Instagram-my treats still remain a distant dream, no longer do we need to salivate with envy over the cute dim sum dishes. Our very own dim sum restaurants has perfected the art of making cute dim sum in Singapore!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"img-responsive alignnone wp-image-366 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/12/cute-dim-sum.png\" alt=\"cute dim sum\" width=\"633\" height=\"627\" />\r\n\r\nDim Sum is a popular form of Chinese cuisine where bite size portions of various foods are served on platters or in baskets. Usually served with drinks, particularly tea, Dim Sum dishes provides a delicious lunch, brunch or snack. With dim sum, you can always have more or less pieces to fill you up as much as you want!\r\n\r\nDim Sum’s small, cute and compact nature lends itself to creativity - you can replicate little animals or cute objects. This has become somewhat of an art and now, we can find tons of really cute Dim Sum in Singapore. If you’re an enthusiast in quest for the coolest, tastiest cute Dim Sum dish in Singapore, here’s a great list for you!\r\n<h2>Cute Dim Sum in Singapore</h2>\r\n<h3>East Ocean Teochew Restaurant</h3>\r\n<img class=\"img-responsive alignnone wp-image-360 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/12/East-Ocean.png\" alt=\"East Ocean\" width=\"701\" height=\"433\" />\r\n\r\nThis awesome little restaurant serves classic and modern Dim Sum dishes in a variety of styles, flavours and designs. Whether you like your Dim Sum steamed, pan-fried or deep-fried, they have an awesome selection that is sure to satisfy. Some notable dishes are the steamed pork BBQ buns with baked varieties available too. There are tarts, baked mini egg desserts and other cute deserts on show and the coolest thing? Kids get amazing animal-shaped dim sum (adults are allowed!) The restaurant itself is cool, usually quite busy and their roast pork and other meats are top class.\r\n\r\nAddress: 391 Orchard Road, #05-08/09 Ngee Ann City, 238872 Singapore\r\n\r\nOpening Hours: Daily, <span class=\"_bC\"><a class=\"fl\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"_Lap\"><span class=\"_Map\">11:30AM–3PM</span></span><span class=\"_Nap\">, </span><span class=\"_Lap\"><span class=\"_Map\">6–11PM</span></span></a></span>\r\n<h3>Mama Panda Kitchen</h3>\r\n<img class=\"img-responsive alignnone wp-image-361 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/12/Mama-Panda-Kitchen.png\" alt=\"Mama Panda Kitchen\" width=\"702\" height=\"465\" />\r\n\r\nThis bistro restaurant is stylish, comfortable and casual and it’s situated within River Safari, Singapore’s amazing river-themed wildlife and leisure park. This restaurant, Mama Panda, lives up to its namesake - it’s serves all things panda related! Their panda styled bao are served in steam baskets and they’re lovely, well design and cute Dim Sum dishes. Awesome for enthusiasts and those looking for a relaxing meal in a great setting.This restaurant rocks for kids who’ll love the cute theme of the entire restaurant and the Dim Sum is colourful and delicious.\r\n\r\nAddress: 80 Mandai Lake Road, River Safari, Giant Panda Forest, Singapore 729826\r\n\r\nOpening Hours: Daily, 10.30am – 6.30pm\r\n<h3>Paradise Teochew Restaurant</h3>\r\n<img class=\"img-responsive alignnone wp-image-362 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/12/Paradise-Teochew-Restaurant.png\" alt=\"Paradise Teochew Restaurant\" width=\"698\" height=\"464\" />\r\n\r\nMore cute Dim Sum now from the Paradise Teochew restaurant in the premises of the Chinese Swimming Club. Their selection of extremely cool, cute and well designed Dim Sum dishes are both tasty and healthy. Check out these little pig Dim Sum custard buns! They look delicious, they ARE delicious! This Teochew restaurant hits all the right notes in its selection of Dim Sum and it has a distinctively cool character which sets it apart from other restaurants.\r\n\r\nAddress: 21 Amber Road, #03-01, Chinese Swimming Club (Arrival Pavilion), Singapore 439870\r\n\r\nTel: +65 6348 7298\r\n\r\nOpening Hours:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Mon to Fri: 11.30am – 3.30pm, 6pm – 10.30pm</li>\r\n 	<li>Sat, Sun &amp; PH: 10.30am – 3.30pm, 6pm – 10.30pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Steam Box</h3>\r\n<img class=\"img-responsive alignnone wp-image-363 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/12/Steam-Box.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"695\" height=\"518\" />\r\n\r\nSteam Box takes a unique and specialist approach to preparing their dishes. They steamboat ingredients at high-speed on a bed of porridge so zhap percolates slowly into it. More meats and seafood steamed for your porridge = a better flavour, simple! Amongst their awesome Dim Sum dishes are these glorious Lotus Paste Bear Buns. It’s a fairly smart restaurant and the fact they steam your meat over rice means your rice-like porridge is both healthy and tasty by the time you come to eat it. Original and tasty!\r\n\r\nAddress: 68 Serangoon Garden Way, Singapore 555962\r\n\r\nOpening hours: Tue-Fri 11am to 3pm, 6pm to 11pm, Sat-Sun 11:30am to 11pm\r\n\r\nTel: 6281 6939\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Majestic Bay</h3>\r\n<img class=\"img-responsive alignnone wp-image-364 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2017/12/Majestic-Bay.png\" alt=\"Majestic Bay\" width=\"697\" height=\"522\" />\r\n\r\nMajestic Bay features a rather classy environment which juxtaposes nicely with its cute Dim Sum. There’s tons of colourful offerings which look stunning and taste delicious. The arty designs of Dim Sum never cease to amaze and here, you can look towards the amazing yellow ducklings filled with Nutella and yams. They’re delightful and they really do look awesome! On top of all these Dim Sum offerings are loads of great seafood dishes including Asia Mud Crabs or US Dungeness Crabs - tasty!\r\n\r\nAddress: 18 Marina Gardens Drive, #01-10, Below Flower Dome, Gardens By The Bay, Singapore 018953\r\n\r\nOpening hours: Mon-Sun 11:30am to 3pm, 5:45pm to 9pm\r\n\r\nTel: 6604 6604\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Know more places to find cute dim sum in Singapore? Let us know in the comments below!</strong>',	'Cute Must-Try Dim Sum in Singapore',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'cute-must-try-dim-sum-in-singapore',	'',	'',	'2017-12-19 15:17:42',	'2017-12-19 07:17:42',	'',	0,	'https://waitrr.com/?p=358',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
