(446,	8,	'2018-01-30 14:29:29',	'2018-01-30 06:29:29',	'Amongst the metropolitan atmosphere that goes some way to define Singapore there are still bastions of quietness situated snugly in backstreets in corners. Book cafes in Singapore offers great environments where anyone can escape for relaxation, coffee, drinks and a bite to eat. Comfortable, cozy and classy, there’s a reading room or book cafe for everyone.\r\n\r\nBook cafes in Singapore have become somewhat of a unique area for meetings. Charity workers, clubs and societies meet in book cafes in Singapore and people are invited to listen, observe or get involved.\r\n\r\nNow, virtually every book cafe is equipped with power points for laptops and phones. Most also have free WiFI. It’s not just books stocked in book cafes, but arrays of magazine, news papers and other publications. Dig in!\r\n<h3>The Reading Room</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_452\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"948\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-452 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/01/The-Reading-Room.png\" alt=\"The Reading Room\" width=\"948\" height=\"629\" /> Photo Source: https://rubbisheatrubbishgrow.com[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis amazing cafe combines sleek furnishings with antiques and art for a tactile comfort that is unique and original. The shelves are stacked out with books and with luxurious seating, you can enjoy your coffee in this renaissance styled cafe. By night, this cafe turns into a bar for a more sophisticated round of drinks.\r\n<div class=\"_eFb\">\r\n<div class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwjDmcrPhv_YAhUfTo8KHbOuCUEQghwoADADegQIABAV\"><span class=\"_xdb\">Address: </span><span class=\"_Xbe\">19 Bukit Pasoh Rd, Singapore 089833</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwjDmcrPhv_YAhUfTo8KHbOuCUEQghwoADADegQIABAV\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwjDmcrPhv_YAhUfTo8KHbOuCUEQghwoADADegQIABAV\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Open Book Cafe</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_454\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"922\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-454 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/01/Open-Book-Cafe.png\" alt=\"Open Book Cafe\" width=\"922\" height=\"691\" /> Photo Source: https://www.tripzilla.com/concept-cafes-bibliophiles-love-singapore/30232[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis book cafe looks like a living room with plush sofas and a dimly lit and warm interior. Simple, cozy and ideal for readers or PC users, this cafe has an isolated quiet room for true bibliophiles. This cafe is also a book retailer and their focus on quality reads really shines through.\r\n\r\n<span class=\"_xdb\">Address: </span><span class=\"_Xbe\">25 Bukit Pasoh Rd, Singapore 089839</span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>The Pigeonhole</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_455\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"550\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-455 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/01/The-Pigeonhole-Cafe.jpg\" alt=\"The Pigeonhole Cafe\" width=\"550\" height=\"366\" /> Photo Source: http://www.ladyironchef.com[/caption]\r\n\r\nHidden in Tanjong Pagar, this awesome book cafe is a long standing favourite for many. This cafe has a cultural vibe and it’s a great meeting point for those involved in the arts or other cultural activity. There are little events and meetings held here and everyone is free to sit, drink and observe or listen.\r\n<div class=\"_eFb\">\r\n<div class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"0ahUKEwjpzu_5hv_YAhXKqY8KHTjgAmAQghwIjAEoADAQ\"><span class=\"_xdb\">Address: </span><span class=\"_Xbe\">52 &amp; 53 Duxton Rd, Singapore 089516</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"0ahUKEwjpzu_5hv_YAhXKqY8KHTjgAmAQghwIjAEoADAQ\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Hungry Heroes</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_456\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"800\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-456 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/01/Hungry-Heroes-1.jpg\" alt=\"Hungry Heroes Cafe\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" /> Photo Source: https://sethlui.com[/caption]\r\n\r\nHungry Heroes is an awesome superhero themed cafe adorned with all manner of film memorabilia from superhero films throughout the ages. The restaurant specializes in delicious meat cuts and chips. Quirky and tasty! Hungry Heroes is perfect for film lovers and film discussions are held often.\r\n<div class=\"_eFb\">\r\n<div class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"0ahUKEwibqJmFh__YAhWMLY8KHTcCCD8QghwIpgEoADAV\"><span class=\"_xdb\">Address: </span><span class=\"_Xbe\">33 Tessensohn Rd, Singapore 217656</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Central P.E.R.K</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_457\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1488\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-457 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/01/Central-Perk-SG.png\" alt=\"Central Perk SG\" width=\"1488\" height=\"843\" /> Photo Source: http://www.centralperk.sg/[/caption]\r\n\r\nIf you love the US sitcom friends then you’ll recognise some features of this quirky cafe. You can find replica pieces from the famous hit TV show and enjoy yourself like Joey, Phoebe, Chandler and co in this quirky central cafe. With a real american theme, this cafe is sure to satisfy any lover of unique cafe spaces.\r\n<div class=\"_eFb\">\r\n<div class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"0ahUKEwiM88eRh__YAhUIo48KHbLjBOsQghwIvQEoADAU\"><span class=\"_xdb\">Address: </span><span class=\"_Xbe\">1 Magazine Road, Central Mall #01-01, Singapore 059567</span></div>\r\n<h3 class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"0ahUKEwiM88eRh__YAhUIo48KHbLjBOsQghwIvQEoADAU\"></h3>\r\n<h3 class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"0ahUKEwiM88eRh__YAhUIo48KHbLjBOsQghwIvQEoADAU\">Grassroots Book Room</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_458\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1104\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-458 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/01/Grassroots-Book-Room.png\" alt=\"Grassroots Book Room\" width=\"1104\" height=\"781\" /> Photo Source: https://www.facebook.com/grassrootsbookroom/[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis book safe is simple, elegant and plainly unpretentious. There’s no super-trendy vibe here and that’s attractive and heaps of cool in itself. The books are well stocked, well chosen and range from classic pieces of literature to popular modern books.\r\n<div class=\"_eFb\">\r\n<div class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"0ahUKEwjNjaSnh__YAhXMq48KHXZWDfQQghwIogEoADAU\"><span class=\"_xdb\">Address: </span><span class=\"_Xbe\">25 Bukit Pasoh Rd, Singapore 089839</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Look See Look See</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_459\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1500\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-459\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/01/Looksee_Facade.jpg\" alt=\"Looksee\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1269\" /> Photo Source: http://www.lobehold.com/looksee/[/caption]\r\n\r\nLocated in the Beach Road shophouse, this lovely little reading room serves a wondrous range of special teas. There are rows and rows of interesting books dispersed throughout the premises. A true space for that all important relaxation and rejuvenation, Look See Look See is a must-visit cafe\r\n<div class=\"_eFb\">\r\n<div class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"0ahUKEwjL06mzh__YAhXGQY8KHTnZCRsQghwInwEoADAU\"><span class=\"_xdb\">Address: </span><span class=\"_Xbe\">267 Beach Rd, Singapore 199545</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;',	'Cozy and Comfy Book Cafes in Singapore',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'book-cafes-in-singapore',	'',	'',	'2018-01-30 14:31:00',	'2018-01-30 06:31:00',	'',	0,	'https://waitrr.com/?p=446',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(447,	8,	'2018-01-30 10:30:47',	'2018-01-30 02:30:47',	'Amongst the metropolitan atmosphere that goes some way to define Singapore there are still bastions of quietness situated snugly in backstreets in corners. The humble book cafe offers quieter environments where people can escape for relaxation, coffee, drinks and a bite to eat. Comfortable, cozy and classy or simple and unpretentious, there’s a reading room or book cafe for everyone.\r\n\r\nBook cafes have become somewhat of a unique area for meetings. Charity workers, clubs and societies meet in book cafes around Singapore and people are invited to listen, observe or get involved.\r\n\r\nNow, virtually every book cafe is equipped with power points for laptops and phones. Most also have free WiFI. It’s not just books stocked in book cafes, but arrays of magazine, news papers and other publications. Dig in!\r\n<h3>The Reading Room</h3>\r\nThis amazing cafe combines sleek furnishings with antiques and art for a tactile comfort that is unique and original. The shelves are stacked out with books and with luxurious seating, you can enjoy your coffee in this renaissance styled cafe. By night, this cafe turns into a bar for a more sophisticated round of drinks.\r\n<h3>Open Book Cafe</h3>\r\nThis book cafe looks like a living room with plush sofas and a dimly lit and warm interior. Simple, cozy and ideal for readers or PC users, this cafe has an isolated quiet room for true bibliophiles. This cafe is also a book retailer and their focus on quality reads really shines through.\r\n<h3>The Pigeonhole</h3>\r\nHidden in Tanjong Pagar, this awesome book cafe is a long standing favourite for many. This cafe has a cultural vibe and it’s a great meeting point for those involved in the arts or other cultural activity. There are little events and meetings held here and everyone is free to sit, drink and observe or listen.\r\n<h3>Hungry Heroes</h3>\r\nHungry Heroes is an awesome superhero themed cafe adorned with all manner of film memorabilia from superhero films throughout the ages. The restaurant specializes in delicious meat cuts and chips. Quirky and tasty! Hungry Heroes is perfect for film lovers and film discussions are held often.\r\n<h3>Central P.E.R.K</h3>\r\nIf you love the US sitcom friends then you’ll recognise some features of this quirky cafe. You can find replica pieces from the famous hit TV show and enjoy yourself like Joey, Phoebe, Chandler and co in this quirky central cafe. With a real american theme, this cafe is sure to satisfy any lover of unique cafe spaces.\r\n<h3>The Lab</h3>\r\nAnother awesome and quirky cafe. The Lab draws its inspiration from Breaking Bad. The interior is stunningly designed to resemble a laboratory and the drinks, served with flavours you can inject with syringes are truly unique. The Lab’s cool interior is unforgettable!\r\n<h3>Grassroots Book Room</h3>\r\nThis book safe is simple, elegant and plainly unpretentious. There’s no super-trendy vibe here and that’s attractive and heaps of cool in itself. The books are well stocked, well chosen and range from classic pieces of literature to popular modern books.\r\n<h3>Books Actually</h3>\r\nMinimalist, sleek and stylish, the book cafe focuses on fiction, poetry and other forms of literature. Prim and proper, you’ll find tons of enjoyment stooping round this lovely book cafe. Relaxing music plays in the background soothing your stay just that little bit more.\r\n<h3>Look See Look See</h3>\r\nLocated in the Beach Road shophouse, this lovely little reading room serves a wondrous range of special teas. There are rows and rows of interesting books dispersed throughout the premises. A true space for that all important relaxation and rejuvenation, Look See Look See is a must-visit cafe.\r\n<h3>Lowercase</h3>\r\nThis cozy space is open with large glass windows providing a bright area for drinkers and readers alike. Famous gelato fills the menu - the Cocktail Caribbean flavour is especially well regarded!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;',	'Book Cafes in Singapore',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'446-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2018-01-30 10:30:47',	'2018-01-30 02:30:47',	'',	446,	'https://waitrr.com/446-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(448,	8,	'2018-02-26 04:20:21',	'2018-02-25 20:20:21',	'Fusion dishes have helped fill unique spots on menus with flare and originality. Fusion food in Singapore has been a hit with everyone since the cooking style was first explored.\r\n\r\nThe term fusion cooking has been thrown about rather flippantly since its conception in the 70’s. Whilst cooking was usually always culturally aligned to just a few styles, it’s now far more liberal and experimental. Who dares, wins!\r\n\r\nChefs use fusion cooking to broaden their repertoire and to add truly unique dishes to their lineups. Over time, some notable mainstream fusion cooking examples include Chinese takeaways in the UK who also serve traditional fish and chips. Now, we have dishes which really are fused together on the same plate. Spaghetti with curry meatballs, stir fry and chips and Mexican ravioli are all awesome examples of fusion dishes that really are tasty to match their criss-crossed nature.\r\n\r\nChefs today are looking to experiment fusion food in Singapore. There will always be many, many restaurants serving the more traditional and classic dishes which are enjoyed by almost everyone but we now, have arrays of fusion restaurants in Singapore which provide some gorgeous tasting, lovely looking and at times, downright outrageous dishes.\r\n<h3>CreatureS Restaurant</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_501\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"866\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-501 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/candlenut.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"866\" height=\"575\" /> Photo Source: https://sethlui.com/candlenut-entertainer-restaurant-review/[/caption]\r\n\r\nCreatures, situated in little India is a famous fusion restaurant with a fine atmosphere and some great dishes to match their sleek styling. Their motive is to fuse Asian and Western food with flair and passion whilst ensuring that their dishes are actually highly researched and well-thought out. One such example is their Urban Baba Babi Pongteh, a slow-cooked pork belly dish in tao jio, all served with a French baguette!\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/fortheloveofcreatures/\">https://www.facebook.com/fortheloveofcreatures/ </a>\r\n<h3>Quentin’s Eurasian Restaurant</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_504\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"870\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-504 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/Quentin.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"870\" height=\"432\" /> Photo Source: https://www.chope.co/singapore-restaurants/restaurant/quentins-eurasian-restaurant[/caption]\r\n\r\nQuentin’s Eurasian Restaurant seeks to take decades of home Eurasian cuisine and put it all into a considered menu that is full to the brim with great dishes, some well-known classic dinners and some funky new takes on classics. The portions are huge and with dishes like fish Bostador, Porki Tembreneu and fried Okra, there’s nothing lacking. The chef takes enormous pride in his menu and each dish is developed with a careful balance and eye for innovation.\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/quentinsrestaurant/\">https://www.facebook.com/quentinsrestaurant/</a>\r\n<h3>Folks Collective</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_506\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"868\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-506 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/the-folks.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"868\" height=\"573\" /> Photo Source: http://kellynwrites.com/2013/07/27/twenty-forth-%E2%9C%98-folks-collective/[/caption]\r\n\r\nFolk’s Collective is a vintage styled restaurant situated in the fringes of Singapore’s CBD. With a classic, warm and atmospheric interior and fusion cuisine based on Thai dishes, this restaurant has earnt some superb reviews.\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/folkscollective/\">https://www.facebook.com/folkscollective/</a>\r\n<h3>The Tuck Shop</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_507\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1073\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-507 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/tuck-shop.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"1073\" height=\"713\" /> Photo Source: http://www.thetuckshop.com.sg/gallery?lightbox=dataItem-j5rswqua4[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis riverside restaurant and all-round hang out is situated on Guillemard road in Singapore. Some of their dishes are fully customised and the Boozy Brunch section of the menu hosts some really funky takes on lagers and beers. One is a lager with fresh calamansi juice and the subtle flavours of Gula Melaka. Other dishes include chilli crab and there’s tons of various salads, vegetarian options and lunchtime classics.\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tuckshopcoffee/\">https://www.facebook.com/tuckshopcoffee/</a>\r\n<h3>North South East West Fusion Vegetarian Cuisine</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_503\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"772\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-503 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/NSEW.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"772\" height=\"570\" /> Photo Source: https://hungryangmo.com/2011/10/north-south-east-west-vegetarian/[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis amazing fusion restaurant has earnt itself some superb reviews. Like its name suggests, it covers all manner of international cuisine. It’s a highly regarded vegetarian restaurant and one of its signature dishes, the Hainanese Beef Noodle, is known for its large portions of thick broth noodles with great mock beef derived from mushroom stems. The hotdogs are great and the mock chicken dishes really hit the spot!\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/North-South-East-West-Fusion-Vegetarian-212697975467114/\">https://www.facebook.com/North-South-East-West-Fusion-Vegetarian-212697975467114/</a>\r\n<h3>Candlenut</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_508\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"866\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-508 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/candlenut-1.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"866\" height=\"575\" /> Photo Source: https://sethlui.com/candlenut-entertainer-restaurant-review/[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis restaurant was only just recently awarded a much-sought after Michelin Star. That says it all really - the dishes here are superb. Classic Peranakan dishes are mixed up with other cuisine delightfully. One such dish is the Assam Sea Bass fillet. Candlenut is exquisite dining for any fusion fan!\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/candlenut.sg/\">https://www.facebook.com/candlenut.sg/</a>\r\n<h3>Sunday Market</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_505\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"915\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-505 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/sunday-market.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"915\" height=\"663\" /> Photo Source: https://www.burpple.com/f/Z3S09-Sj[/caption]\r\n\r\nTucked away with a superbly designed and comfy interior, this fusion restaurant is quirky and features some great dishes that satisfy even the quirkiest customers. You can tuck into some Tom Yam spaghetti with seafood and enoki mushrooms or a miso-marinated dish cheekily named “I’ll Find Salmon Like You”.\r\n\r\nHungryGoWhere: <a href=\"http://www.hungrygowhere.com/singapore/sunday-market-sengkang-hougang-buangkok/\">http://www.hungrygowhere.com/singapore/sunday-market-sengkang-hougang-buangkok/</a>\r\n<h3>Ding Dong</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_509\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"817\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-509 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/Dingdong.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"817\" height=\"546\" /> Photo Source: http://www.sgfoodonfoot.com/2017/06/ding-dong-amoy-street-refreshes-local.html[/caption]\r\n\r\nDing Dong accomplishes the brave with fine fusions inspired by Southeast Asian cuisine. Some real decadent dishes include tune loin with green papaya and sour sauce or crispy pork trotter. Some awesome but slightly crazy cocktails join the lineup, including vodka cocktails with chilli brine and vermouth with rice-chip. Ding dong!\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/dingdongsingapore/\">https://www.facebook.com/dingdongsingapore/</a>\r\n<h3>Chop Suey</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_514\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"726\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-514 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/chop-suey.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"726\" height=\"539\" /> Photo Source: http://chubbyhubby.net/restaurants/chopsuey-Ohoto Scafe-cool-kitsch-chinesey-food-in-singapore/[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis restaurant provides a fine yet familiar Anglo-Chinese menu with plenty of classic Chinese dishes and chip-shop style spring rolls, fish dishes and sticky quail legs amongst some other fusion oddities. Top in quality and awesome in originality, Chop Suey achieves some fantastic dishes.\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/chopsueywa/\">https://www.facebook.com/chopsueywa/</a>\r\n<h3>Nuvo</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_512\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"928\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-512 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/nuvo.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"928\" height=\"635\" /> Photo Source: http://vanillaluxury.sg/magazine/nuvo-italian-japanese-contemporary-restaurant-customs-house[/caption]\r\n\r\nNuvo is a real pioneer of nouveau fusion cuisine in Singapore and focuses on a finely balanced Italian-Japanese menu. The Blackened Soyu River Prawn is a highly regarded dish and is combined with seared pancetta sea-scallops and Mikan glazed carrots. The dishes are exquisitely displayed in all their glory - a real quality restaurant.\r\n\r\nFacebook:<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/NUVONews/\"> https://www.facebook.com/NUVONews/</a>\r\n<h3>Eight Cafe &amp; Bar</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_510\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"769\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-510 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/eight-cafe.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"769\" height=\"569\" /> Photo Source: http://www.jbabiesinthedaisies.com/2013/04/eight-cafe-bar.html[/caption]\r\n\r\nEight Cafe and Bar, situated along Bukit Pasoh, is an awesome vintage-styled restaurant with a particularly appealing interior. Their dishes range from classic to fusion dishes like the House Special Crispy Brown Rice Risotto which is blended delightfully with seafood and an array of tasty Asian herbs.\r\n\r\nFacebook:<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/eightcafebar/\"> https://www.facebook.com/eightcafebar/</a>\r\n<h3>Platypus Kitchen</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_513\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"994\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-513 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/platypus.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"994\" height=\"552\" /> Photo Source: http://thesmartlocal.com/sg/western-restaurants/7897-platypus-kitchen[/caption]\r\n\r\nPlatypus Kitchen was founded on the principle of providing gourmet dining for affordable prices. Their fusion style of cuisine is fuelled by Asian dishes and features iron-grilled meat cuts, risottos and pastas of all kinds. Their pastas are flavoured with Asian sauces and herbs and many feature fresh additions and adornings of summer and winter fruits, depending on the season.\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/PlatypusKitchen/\">https://www.facebook.com/PlatypusKitchen/</a>\r\n<h3>Kitchen by Food Rebel</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_511\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"866\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-511 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/02/Food-Rebel.png\" alt=\"fusion food in singapore waitrr\" width=\"866\" height=\"570\" /> Photo Source: https://therantingpanda.com/2016/09/14/food-review-kitchen-by-food-rebel-healthy-eating-at-stanley-street-in-cbd/[/caption]\r\n\r\nFood Rebel’s aren’t rebels without a cause, as their motive is to create incredibly healthy dishes from fresh ingredients. Some of their fusion dishes sound awesome, like the Aussie beef Bolognese. Their dishes are finely tuned and with an excellent set of add-ons and some awesome herbal and medicinal drinks, Food Rebel achieves their healthy aims easily.\r\n\r\nFacebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/kitchenbyfoodrebel/\">https://www.facebook.com/kitchenbyfoodrebel/</a>',	'13 Fusion Food In Singapore You Need to Try',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'fusion-food-in-singapore',	'',	'',	'2018-02-22 14:20:43',	'2018-02-22 06:20:43',	'',	0,	'https://waitrr.com/?p=448',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(449,	8,	'2018-01-30 13:32:45',	'2018-01-30 05:32:45',	'Fusion dishes have helped fill unique spots on menus with flare and originality.\r\n\r\nThe term fusion cooking has been thrown about rather flippantly since its conception in the 70’s. Whilst cooking was usually always culturally aligned to just a few styles, it’s now far more liberal and experimental. Who dares wins! Chefs use fusion cooking to broaden their repertoire and to add truly unique dishes to their lineups. Over time, some notable mainstream fusion cooking examples include Chinese takeaways in the UK who also serve traditional fish and chips. Now, we have dishes which really are fused together on the same plate. Spaghetti with curry meatballs, stir fry and chips and Mexican ravioli are all awesome examples of fusion dishes that really are tasty to match their criss-crossed nature.\r\n\r\nChefs today are looking to experiment. There will always be many, many restaurants serving the more traditional and classic dishes which are enjoyed by almost everyone but we now, have arrays of fusion restaurants in Singapore which provide some gorgeous tasting, lovely looking and at times, downright outrageous dishes.\r\n<h3>CreatureS Restaurant</h3>\r\nCreatures, situated in little India is a famous fusion restaurant with a fine atmosphere and some great dishes to match their sleek styling. Their motive is to fuse Asian and Western food with flair and passion whilst ensuring that their dishes are actually highly researched and well-thought out. One such example is their Urban Baba Babi Pongteh, a slow-cooked pork belly dish in tao jio, all served with a French baguette!\r\n<h3>Quentin’s Eurasian Restaurant</h3>\r\nQuentin’s Eurasian Restaurant seeks to take decades of home Eurasian cuisine and put it all into a considered menu that is full to the brim with great dishes, some well-known classic dinners and some funky new takes on classics. The portions are huge and with dishes like fish Bostador, Porki Tembreneu and fried Okra, there’s nothing lacking. The chef takes enormous pride in his menu and each dish is developed with a careful balance and eye for innovation\r\n<h3>Folks Collective</h3>\r\nFolk’s Collective is a vintage styled restaurant situated in the fringes of Singapore’s CBD. With a classic, warm and atmospheric interior and fusion cuisine based on Thai dishes, this restaurant has earnt some superb reviews.\r\n<h3>The Tuck Shop</h3>\r\nThis riverside restaurant and all-round hang out is situated on Guillemard road in Singapore. Some of their dishes are fully customised and the Boozy Brunch section of the menu hosts some really funky takes on lagers and beers. One is a lager with fresh calamansi juice and the subtle flavours of Gula Melaka. Other dishes include chilli crab and there’s tons of various salads, vegetarian options and lunchtime classics.\r\n<h3>North South East West Fusion Vegetarian Cuisine</h3>\r\nThis amazing fusion restaurant has earnt itself some superb reviews. Like its name suggests, it covers all manner of international cuisine. It’s a highly regarded vegetarian restaurant and one of its signature dishes, the Hainanese Beef Noodle, is known for its large portions of thick broth noodles with great mock beef derived from mushroom stems. The hotdogs are great and the mock chicken dishes really hit the spot!\r\n<h3>Candlenut</h3>\r\nThis restaurant was only just recently awarded a much-sought after Michelin Star. That says it all really - the dishes here are superb. Classic Peranakan dishes are mixed up with other cuisine delightfully. One such dish is the Assam Sea Bass fillet. Candlenut is exquisite dining for any fusion fan!\r\n<h3>Sunday Market</h3>\r\nTucked away with a superbly designed and comfy interior, this fusion restaurant is quirky and features some great dishes that satisfy even the quirkiest customers. You can tuck into some Tom Yam spaghetti with seafood and enoki mushrooms or a miso-marinated dish cheekily named “I’ll Find Salmon Like You”.\r\n<h3>Ding Dong</h3>\r\nDing Dong accomplishes the brave with fine fusions inspired by Southeast Asian cuisine. Some real decadent dishes include tune loin with green papaya and sour sauce or crispy pork trotter. Some awesome but slightly crazy cocktails join the lineup, including vodka cocktails with chilli brine and vermouth with rice-chip. Ding dong!\r\n<h3>Chop Suey</h3>\r\nThis restaurant provides a fine yet familiar Anglo-Chinese menu with plenty of classic Chinese dishes and chip-shop style spring rolls, fish dishes and sticky quail legs amongst some other fusion oddities. Top in quality and awesome in originality, Chop Suey achieves some fantastic dishes.\r\n<h3>Nuvo</h3>\r\nNuvo is a real pioneer of nouveau fusion cuisine in Singapore and focuses on a finely balanced Italian-Japanese menu. The Blackened Soyu River Prawn is a highly regarded dish and is combined with seared pancetta sea-scallops and Mikan glazed carrots. The dishes are exquisitely displayed in all their glory - a real quality restaurant.\r\n<h3>Restaurant Ember</h3>\r\nRestaurant Ember combines European cuisine with intelligent Asian influences. The chef is well known and has plied his trade to this new form of fusion cooking with remarkable results. One such notable dish is the French Bouillabaisse with Hokkaido scallops.\r\n<h3>Eight Cafe &amp; Bar</h3>\r\nEight Cafe and Bar, situated along Bukit Pasoh, is an awesome vintage-styled restaurant with a particularly appealing interior. Their dishes range from classic to fusion dishes like the House Special Crispy Brown Rice Risotto which is blended delightfully with seafood and an array of tasty Asian herbs.\r\n<h3>Platypus Kitchen</h3>\r\nPlatypus Kitchen was founded on the principle of providing gourmet dining for affordable prices. Their fusion style of cuisine is fuelled by Asian dishes and features iron-grilled meat cuts, risottos and pastas of all kinds. Their pastas are flavoured with Asian sauces and herbs and many feature fresh additions and adornings of summer and winter fruits, depending on the season.\r\n<h3>Kitchen by Food Rebel</h3>\r\nFood Rebel’s aren’t rebels without a cause, as their motive is to create incredibly healthy dishes from fresh ingredients. Some of their fusion dishes sound awesome, like the Aussie beef Bolognese. Their dishes are finely tuned and with an excellent set of add-ons and some awesome herbal and medicinal drinks, Food Rebel achieves their healthy aims easily.',	'Fusion Food In Singapore',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'448-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2018-01-30 13:32:45',	'2018-01-30 05:32:45',	'',	448,	'https://waitrr.com/448-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
