(451,	8,	'2018-01-30 13:34:27',	'2018-01-30 05:34:27',	'Amongst the metropolitan atmosphere that goes some way to define Singapore there are still bastions of quietness situated snugly in backstreets in corners. Book cafes in Singapore offers great environments where anyone can escape for relaxation, coffee, drinks and a bite to eat. Comfortable, cozy and classy, there’s a reading room or book cafe for everyone.\r\n\r\nBook cafes in Singapore have become somewhat of a unique area for meetings. Charity workers, clubs and societies meet in book cafes in Singapore and people are invited to listen, observe or get involved.\r\n\r\nNow, virtually every book cafe is equipped with power points for laptops and phones. Most also have free WiFI. It’s not just books stocked in book cafes, but arrays of magazine, news papers and other publications. Dig in!\r\n<h3>The Reading Room</h3>\r\nThis amazing cafe combines sleek furnishings with antiques and art for a tactile comfort that is unique and original. The shelves are stacked out with books and with luxurious seating, you can enjoy your coffee in this renaissance styled cafe. By night, this cafe turns into a bar for a more sophisticated round of drinks.\r\n<h3>Open Book Cafe</h3>\r\nThis book cafe looks like a living room with plush sofas and a dimly lit and warm interior. Simple, cozy and ideal for readers or PC users, this cafe has an isolated quiet room for true bibliophiles. This cafe is also a book retailer and their focus on quality reads really shines through.\r\n<h3>The Pigeonhole</h3>\r\nHidden in Tanjong Pagar, this awesome book cafe is a long standing favourite for many. This cafe has a cultural vibe and it’s a great meeting point for those involved in the arts or other cultural activity. There are little events and meetings held here and everyone is free to sit, drink and observe or listen.\r\n<h3>Hungry Heroes</h3>\r\nHungry Heroes is an awesome superhero themed cafe adorned with all manner of film memorabilia from superhero films throughout the ages. The restaurant specializes in delicious meat cuts and chips. Quirky and tasty! Hungry Heroes is perfect for film lovers and film discussions are held often.\r\n<h3>Central P.E.R.K</h3>\r\nIf you love the US sitcom friends then you’ll recognise some features of this quirky cafe. You can find replica pieces from the famous hit TV show and enjoy yourself like Joey, Phoebe, Chandler and co in this quirky central cafe. With a real american theme, this cafe is sure to satisfy any lover of unique cafe spaces.\r\n<h3>The Lab</h3>\r\nAnother awesome and quirky cafe. The Lab draws its inspiration from Breaking Bad. The interior is stunningly designed to resemble a laboratory and the drinks, served with flavours you can inject with syringes are truly unique. The Lab’s cool interior is unforgettable!\r\n<h3>Grassroots Book Room</h3>\r\nThis book safe is simple, elegant and plainly unpretentious. There’s no super-trendy vibe here and that’s attractive and heaps of cool in itself. The books are well stocked, well chosen and range from classic pieces of literature to popular modern books.\r\n<h3>Books Actually</h3>\r\nMinimalist, sleek and stylish, the book cafe focuses on fiction, poetry and other forms of literature. Prim and proper, you’ll find tons of enjoyment stooping round this lovely book cafe. Relaxing music plays in the background soothing your stay just that little bit more.\r\n<h3>Look See Look See</h3>\r\nLocated in the Beach Road shophouse, this lovely little reading room serves a wondrous range of special teas. There are rows and rows of interesting books dispersed throughout the premises. A true space for that all important relaxation and rejuvenation, Look See Look See is a must-visit cafe.\r\n<h3>Lowercase</h3>\r\nThis cozy space is open with large glass windows providing a bright area for drinkers and readers alike. Famous gelato fills the menu - the Cocktail Caribbean flavour is especially well regarded!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;',	'Book Cafes in Singapore',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'446-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2018-01-30 13:34:27',	'2018-01-30 05:34:27',	'',	446,	'https://waitrr.com/446-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
