3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"2ahUKEwjDmcrPhv_YAhUfTo8KHbOuCUEQghwoADADegQIABAV\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Open Book Cafe</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_454\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"922\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-454 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/01/Open-Book-Cafe.png\" alt=\"Open Book Cafe\" width=\"922\" height=\"691\" /> Photo Source: https://www.tripzilla.com/concept-cafes-bibliophiles-love-singapore/30232[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis book cafe looks like a living room with plush sofas and a dimly lit and warm interior. Simple, cozy and ideal for readers or PC users, this cafe has an isolated quiet room for true bibliophiles. This cafe is also a book retailer and their focus on quality reads really shines through.\r\n\r\n<span class=\"_xdb\">Address: </span><span class=\"_Xbe\">25 Bukit Pasoh Rd, Singapore 089839</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>The Pigeonhole</h3>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_455\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"550\"]<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-455 size-full\" src=\"https://waitrr.com/app/uploads/2018/01/The-Pigeonhole-Cafe.jpg\" alt=\"The Pigeonhole Cafe\" width=\"550\" height=\"366\" /> Photo Source: http://www.ladyironchef.com[/caption]\r\n\r\nHidden in Tanjong Pagar, this awesome book cafe is a long standing favourite for many. This cafe has a cultural vibe and it’s a great meeting point for those involved in the arts or other cultural activity. There are little events and meetings held here and everyone is free to sit, drink and observe or listen.\r\n<div class=\"_eFb\">\r\n<div class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"0ahUKEwjpzu_5hv_YAhXKqY8KHTjgAmAQghwIjAEoADAQ\"><span class=\"_xdb\">Address: </span><span class=\"_Xbe\">52 &amp; 53 Duxton Rd, Singapore 089516</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"_mr kno-fb-ctx\" data-dtype=\"d3adr\" data-local-attribute=\"d3adr\" data-ved=\"0ahUKEwjpzu_5hv_YAhXKqY8KHTjgAmAQghwIjAEoADAQ\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"